## Project Purpose
Vanish is an internal workflow engine that executes flows. Flows contain
tasks, and tasks can call other flows (subflows). Some subflows are only
resolved at runtime via Jinja templating — so the full dependency tree
of any flow is not statically knowable.

`vanish-reporting` mines historical job execution data to build an
empirical dependency graph. By analyzing enough past jobs, we can
discover which flows call which other flows, how deep the chains go,
and which paths were actually executed.

